<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659.119/354</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-06T18:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>958. Your 2452, June 29, noon. Whenever in your sound discretion it
                                appears advisable, War Trade Board will license for prompt shipment
                                2,000 tons wrought iron tubing, and if you find it will be of
                                service in the situation described in your wire you may intimate
                                that at your request we would be willing to go further in iron and
                                steel materials.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>